While phonology (sound system), morphology and lexis (word formation and the inventory of words), syntax (sentence formation), and semantics (meaning) describe the discrete combinatorial system underlying language, pragmatics situates that very system in social context. The following is concerned with how pragmatics provides insight into culture, defined here as the shared conventions of speaking and interaction in a given language community. 


